/* lecture 7 The CSS Inheritance & Specificity */

/* how to inheritence a selector */
/* inherit is used in place of color of a child styling it takes same the color given to the parent element */
p{
  color: white;
}

.p2{
  color: inherit;
}


/* specificity */
/* type selector is specified will over ride the universal selector */
/* example */
*{
color: black;
background-color: white;
}

.p{
  color: blue;
  background-color: pink;
}/*it over rides the universal selector and gives styling to the p tag */


/* how the stylesheet works */
/* stylesheet works from top to bottom  */
/* stylesheet gives preference to the styling is given at last */

/* "important" keyword is used to give a high preference to the stylesheet */
